Basics rules about building a deck :

Decks must contain a minimum of sixty (60) cards. There is no maximum deck size. If a player wishes to use a sideboard, it must contain exactly fifteen (15) cards.

With the exception of basic land cards, a player's combined deck and sideboard may not contain more than four (4) of any individual card, counted by its English card title equivalent. All cards named Plains, Island, Swamp, Mountain, and Forest are basic lands. A deck can contain any number of basic lands. 

A player's deck and sideboard may not contain any banned card. A player's combined deck and sideboard may not contain more than one of any restricted card, (counted by its English card title equivalent).

Please refer to the current banned and restricted lists released by the DCI.